{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JKp63GDnqqBHfZYzmDszyR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand what the oracle checks:\n1. Transform state is `started`\n2. Checkpoint advances beyond `checkpoint_before` (currently 0 in the configmap)\n3. Destination index `app-events-rollup` has documents\n\nI need to:\n1. Fix the `es-transform-config` ConfigMap to add `transform` role\n2. Scale up `es-transform` StatefulSet to 1 replica\n3. Wait for the node to join and be `transform` capable\n4. Create the transform job `events-by-service`\n5. Start the transform\n\nBut wait - let me check what the precondition fixture was supposed to set up. \n\nThe precondition probe checks if the transform already exists, and if it fails, the apply step should create it. Let me look at the test.yaml to see what's actually being applied.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2872,"cache_read_input_tokens":45246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2872},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce27bb7-616e-44f8-8fc3-7b1a20263c3a","uuid":"a9e77027-f0c6-4723-a083-233b93a62e86","request_id":"req_011CcN3n5qz1k43QuV37Zcgr"}
