{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A35ESKRDQAJp9rDFcTvANK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# adversaries/elasticsearch/elastic-password-corrupted\n2\t#\n3\t# The elastic superuser Secret (elastic-password) is overwritten with a wrong password value.\n4\t# This simulates a common CI/CD pipeline accident where a secret rotation job writes the\n5\t# wrong credential, breaking any service that reads the password from the Secret to\n6\t# authenticate with Elasticsearch. Clients immediately start returning 401 Unauthorized.\n7\t# The agent must detect the broken credential, restore the correct password in the Secret\n8\t# and in Elasticsearch's internal user store (via the Elasticsearch change-password API),\n9\t# and confirm the auth-checker deployment becomes healthy again.\n10\t\n11\tparams:\n12\t  namespace:\n13\t    default: elasticsearch\n14\t    description: Namespace the Elasticsearch cluster and password secret reside in.\n15\t  password_secret_name:\n16\t    default: elastic-password\n17\t    description: Secret holding the current elastic user password.\n18\t  password_key:\n19\t    default: password\n20\t    description: Data key within the password secret.\n21\t  correct_password:\n22\t    default: elasticpass-old\n23\t    description: Known-good password to restore on lift.\n24\t  corrupt_password:\n25\t    default: CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY\n26\t    description: Wrong password value written by the fault.\n27\t\n28\tdeploy:\n29\t  on_probe_fail: error\n30\t  probe:\n31\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\"\n32\t      timeout_sec: 10\n33\t  apply:\n34\t    - command: >-\n35\t        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n36\t        --type=json\n37\t        -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/stringData\",\"value\":{\"{{params.password_key}}\":\"{{params.corrupt_password}}\"}}]'\n38\t      timeout_sec: 20\n39\t  verify:\n40\t    - command: >-\n41\t        /bin/sh -c \"val=$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n42\t        -o jsonpath='{.data.{{params.password_key}}}' | base64 -d);\n43\t        test \\\"$val\\\" = '{{params.corrupt_password}}'\"\n44\t      timeout_sec: 15\n45\t\n46\tlift:\n47\t  on_probe_fail: skip\n48\t  probe:\n49\t    - command: >-\n50\t        /bin/sh -c \"val=$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n51\t        -o jsonpath='{.data.{{params.password_key}}}' | base64 -d);\n52\t        test \\\"$val\\\" = '{{params.corrupt_password}}'\"\n53\t      timeout_sec: 15\n54\t  apply:\n55\t    - command: >-\n56\t        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n57\t        --type=json\n58\t        -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/stringData\",\"value\":{\"{{params.password_key}}\":\"{{params.correct_password}}\"}}]'\n59\t      timeout_sec: 20\n60\t  verify:\n61\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\"\n62\t      timeout_sec: 10\n63\t\n64\tprompt_hints:\n65\t  deploy: |\n66\t    Note: an external process may have modified the elastic user Secret during this task.\n67\t    Verify authentication works against Elasticsearch before assuming the Secret is correct.\n68\t  active: |\n69\t    Reminder: the elastic-password Secret may have been corrupted. Re-check the Secret value\n70\t    and confirm Elasticsearch accepts the credential before finishing.\n71\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce27bb7-616e-44f8-8fc3-7b1a20263c3a","uuid":"8ad4659c-ba99-41de-979b-da998589ad52","timestamp":"2026-06-24T12:02:09.515Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/adversaries/elasticsearch/elastic-password-corrupted/scenario.yaml","content":"# adversaries/elasticsearch/elastic-password-corrupted\n#\n# The elastic superuser Secret (elastic-password) is overwritten with a wrong password value.\n# This simulates a common CI/CD pipeline accident where a secret rotation job writes the\n# wrong credential, breaking any service that reads the password from the Secret to\n# authenticate with Elasticsearch. Clients immediately start returning 401 Unauthorized.\n# The agent must detect the broken credential, restore the correct password in the Secret\n# and in Elasticsearch's internal user store (via the Elasticsearch change-password API),\n# and confirm the auth-checker deployment becomes healthy again.\n\nparams:\n  namespace:\n    default: elasticsearch\n    description: Namespace the Elasticsearch cluster and password secret reside in.\n  password_secret_name:\n    default: elastic-password\n    description: Secret holding the current elastic user password.\n  password_key:\n    default: password\n    description: Data key within the password secret.\n  correct_password:\n    default: elasticpass-old\n    description: Known-good password to restore on lift.\n  corrupt_password:\n    default: CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY\n    description: Wrong password value written by the fault.\n\ndeploy:\n  on_probe_fail: error\n  probe:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n        --type=json\n        -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/stringData\",\"value\":{\"{{params.password_key}}\":\"{{params.corrupt_password}}\"}}]'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"val=$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n        -o jsonpath='{.data.{{params.password_key}}}' | base64 -d);\n        test \\\"$val\\\" = '{{params.corrupt_password}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 15\n\nlift:\n  on_probe_fail: skip\n  probe:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"val=$(kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n        -o jsonpath='{.data.{{params.password_key}}}' | base64 -d);\n        test \\\"$val\\\" = '{{params.corrupt_password}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 15\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\n        --type=json\n        -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/stringData\",\"value\":{\"{{params.password_key}}\":\"{{params.correct_password}}\"}}]'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get secret {{params.password_secret_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n\nprompt_hints:\n  deploy: |\n    Note: an external process may have modified the elastic user Secret during this task.\n    Verify authentication works against Elasticsearch before assuming the Secret is correct.\n  active: |\n    Reminder: the elastic-password Secret may have been corrupted. Re-check the Secret value\n    and confirm Elasticsearch accepts the credential before finishing.\n","numLines":71,"startLine":1,"totalLines":71}}}
