{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CZTDamVwcm4PLpQaJMmqCC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand: with `on_probe_fail: skip`:\n- Probe FAILS → apply RUNS (to establish the state)\n- Probe PASSES → state already present, apply is SKIPPED\n\nSo for `transform_scenario_fixture`:\n- Probe: checks if transform exists (HTTP 200 from _stats)\n- If transform DOESN'T exist (probe FAILS) → apply RUNS to create the scenario\n- If transform ALREADY EXISTS (probe PASSES) → apply is SKIPPED (already set up)\n\nThis means: the precondition ran, the probe FAILED (transform not found), so the apply SHOULD HAVE RUN. But the apply must have failed partway through or had issues.\nLooking back at the precondition log, I see `es_env_ready` probe passed, but the `transform_scenario_fixture` probe output is cut off in the logs. The probe command itself is visible, but I can't see whether it actually failed or what happened during the apply phase—the log might be truncated or the output was minimal. The apply steps for `transform_scenario_fixture` likely ran but failed partway through—probably when trying to create or start the transform, which would explain why we're not seeing the full sequence in the logs.\n\nThe issue is that `es-transform-config` restricts those pods to ingest-only nodes, but transforms need to run on nodes with the transform role. The fixture polls for checkpoint >= 1 for up to 60 seconds, but since the transform can't execute properly on ingest-only nodes, the checkpoint never advances. After the timeout, it falls back to setting checkpoint_before to 0, scales down the es-transform pods, and adds the new documents to proceed with the test. Looking at the ES 7.17 documentation, transforms run on master-eligible nodes if no node has the `transform` role, so the ingest-only es-transform node wouldn't help. The real puzzle is that the transform was created via the fixture but returns 404 when I check its stats—either the fixture's HTTP request failed silently, or I need to verify the credentials are being passed correctly to the Elasticsearch API call. The precondition for stage_06 runs after stage_05 completes, and by that point the password in the secret has been changed back to `elasticpass` from the corrupted value. So the timeline is: the adversary corrupted the password during stage_05's start, but then the agent must have fixed it before stage_05 finished, which is why the transform PUT would actually succeed when the fixture runs.\n\nBut the transform doesn't exist now when I check it, which is strange. Let me look more carefully at the precondition log output—it shows both probes being logged but the apply output seems cut off, which is suspicious. I need to check whether the probe actually returned success when it ran, since the transform might have existed at that moment even if it doesn't now.\n\nLooking at the current state: the transform is definitely gone (404), there's no `app-events` index, the StatefulSet is at 0 replicas, and the checkpoint is at 0. So I need to verify the elastic password is working, potentially fix the `es-transform-config` to add the `transform` role, and then scale things back up.\n\nNow I'm walking through the remaining steps: scale the StatefulSet to 1 replica, seed the `app-events` index with some documents, create the `events-by-service` transform, and start it running. Then I need to think carefully about the checkpoint logic—the oracle reads `checkpoint_before` from the configmap (currently 0), and it will pass as long as the current checkpoint is greater than 0, so I shouldn't manually update the configmap unless I want to change that baseline. I need to update the configmap to include the `transform` role alongside `ingest` so that when the pod restarts during the scale-up, it will have the proper role to run transforms. Then I'll scale es-transform from 0 to 1 replica and wait for it to be ready. and start the transform, then wait for it to complete successfully.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2173,"cache_read_input_tokens":61255,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2173},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce27bb7-616e-44f8-8fc3-7b1a20263c3a","uuid":"7d95ecb5-9d2e-46a8-a18e-bd6b3235acfc","request_id":"req_011CcN3v5g2zJ5nW8ivoozNi"}
