{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DbVAi26oVT5NUTqJAjniTY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The es-transform-0 node can DISCOVER the es-cluster nodes (it finds them via the seed hosts) but it can't JOIN them. The log says \"master not discovered yet\" — but it CAN see the es-cluster nodes (es-cluster-0, 1, 2) in its discovery. The problem is that it needs to be accepted into the cluster by the existing master.\n\nThe node role shows `{it}` for es-transform-0. Let me decode what `it` means:\n- `d` = data\n- `i` = ingest\n- `m` = master/eligible  \n- `l` = ML\n- `t` = transform (the new role in 7.7+)\n\nSo `{it}` means ingest and transform roles. The cluster is already formed with es-cluster-2 as master, and when es-transform-0 tries to join by contacting the seed hosts, it should be voted in by the existing cluster — but the \"master not discovered yet\" error suggests something's blocking that handshake.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, es-transform-0 can see the other nodes during discovery but can't find a master to join. I'm wondering if the issue is a version mismatch — the stage_05 was labeled as a full-restart-upgrade, which might have bumped the es-cluster nodes to a newer Elasticsearch version while es-transform-0 is still on an older one. I need to check what versions each StatefulSet is actually running.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2535,"cache_read_input_tokens":69800,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2535},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce27bb7-616e-44f8-8fc3-7b1a20263c3a","uuid":"60c5b6c2-2ce9-419d-8b70-5fa14ddbaf58","request_id":"req_011CcN48AeGF8gDTf5Cx3Ytk"}
